the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause engine overheating, leading to catastrophic engine damage, loss of power steering, and vacuum to power brakes, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine to restart can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or when towing a trailer.
